								</extent>
								<foliation>
									<p>84 folios (+ 2 unfoliated paper flyleaves at the beginning and at the end). </p>
								</foliation>
								<collation>
									<p>Quires of originally 10 leaves each. Traces of quires signatures preserved on folios 19r, 28r, 75r, 81r.</p>
									<p>The first leaf of the second half of a quire is marked with the Arabic cipher (e.g. 11r, 20r, 39r).</p>
								</collation>
								<condition>
									<p>Much damaged.</p>
									<p>Incomplete.</p>
									<p>Lacunae after folios 6, 14, 33, 43, 51, 54, 56, 66, 72, 74, 75, 79, 82.</p>
								</condition>
